One rearguard action after this battle was defeated at the Battle of Kip’s Landing,
though John Glover’s Marblehead fishermen provided a more successful rearguard at Pell’s
Point. General Alexander Stirling was captured at this battle, where the Gowanus Heights
were fortified by (+) Israel Putnam but the Jamaica Road was left unguarded. That road
was used by Henry Clinton to outflank the American defenders, although he let them escape
after declining to attack (*) Brooklyn Heights. For the point, name this August 1776 Revolutionary
War battle, after which George Washington lost control of New York.=====
Battle of Long Island =====